  • Method Details

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      The main method of the Implementor class.

      If 2 arguments provided, implements the given interface args[0] and creates the implementation class .java file in the path args[1].

      If 3 arguments provided and args[0] is "-jar", implements the given interface args[1] and creates .jar file with the implementation class .class file in the path args[2].

      Parameters:
      args - command line arguments String array.

      Implements the given interface token and creates .java file in root directory.
      Specified by:

      Parameters:

      root - root directory Path of the created file.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if token is not an interface, or it is private, or an error occurred with root path.

    • implementJar

      public void implementJar(Class<?> token, Path jarFile) throws ImplerException
      Implements the given interface token and creates .jar file with .class file of the implementation class in root directory.

      Creates a temporary directory for .java and .class files and then deletes it.

      Specified by:
      implementJar in interface JarImpler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      jarFile - target .jar file Path.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if an error occurred with jarFile path, or if an implementation error occurred, or if a compiling error occurred, or if a .jar file creation error occurred.
